      "section": "teaser",
      "speaker": "pixel",
      "speaker_mode": "narration",
      "text": "I'd seen enough broken Pillars to know that once they shatter, they die. The pieces go dark within hours—Signal draining away like water from a cracked vessel. Cold stone, nothing more. Archaeological curiosities for people with more time than sense.",
