      "section": "teaser",
      "speaker": "pixel",
      "speaker_mode": "narration",
      "text": "But there it was in the grainy photograph Kess had sent: a Pillar fragment the size of a barrel, cradled in a Driftborn woman's weathered hands, pulsing with steady blue-white light. The kind of glow that said alive. The kind of glow that said impossible.",
